    "description": {
      "value": "<div><div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>You can spend 2 ki points as an action to create a whip of water that shoves and pulls a creature to unbalance it. A creature that you can see that is within 30 feet of you must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, the creature takes [[/damage 3d10 type=bludgeoning]] damage, plus an extra [[/damage 1d10 type=bludgeoning]] damage for each additional ki point you spend, and you can either knock it &amp;Reference[condition=prone] or pull it up to 25 feet closer to you. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage, and you don't pull it or knock it &amp;Reference[condition=prone].</p></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div></div>",
      "chat": ""
    },
